01/02/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- In a speech to the European Parliament on Wednesday (January 31st), Romanian President Traian Basescu said his country has continued with reforms in the weeks since EU accession, and that the authorities as well as the Romanian public are well aware that the actual process of integration has barely begun. 
In terms of priorities, Basescu cited economic growth, effective institutions, an infrastructure that meets EU standards, a cleaner environment and rooting out corruption. 
(Ziua - 01/02/07; Rompres, EU Observer - 31/01/07)
